Ghana Attracts $552.3 Million in Foreign Direct Investment in 2nd Quarter

-- B y   E k o w   D o n t o h
-- 
2011-08-04T13:10:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/ghana-attracts-552-3-million-in-foreign-direct-investment-in-2nd-quarter.html
Ghana attracted $552.3 million in
foreign direct investment in the second quarter as  China  stepped
up the number of its projects in the West African nation.  Investment increased from $351.8 million in the previous
three months, the Ghana Investment Promotion Centre said in a
statement handed to reporters today in Accra, the capital. The
inflow of funds rose from $161.3 million in the fourth quarter.  The number of investment projects increased to 127 in the
second quarter from 109 in the previous three months, with the
Chinese accounting for 23, up from 13, George Aboagye, chief
executive officer of the Ghana investment promotion centre, told
reporters.  The Netherlands recorded the largest value of investments
at $128.3 million.  The investment projects generated 14,412 jobs, the agency
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 